parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the steering wheel to become stiff or difficult to turn, increasing the risk of a crash or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering warning light illuminates
the steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn
the vehicle is hard to maneuver
the power steering fails intermittently
the vehicle requires excessive force to steer
the power steering warning chime sounds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety issues, including loss of headlights, brake lights, and other essential systems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Headlights burning out or melting
brake lights staying on or not working
door locks malfunctioning
horn sounding without warning
and warning indicators on the instrument panel illuminating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the BCM can cause various electrical systems to malfunction, including headlights, brake lights, and door locks, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Headlights not working
brake lights staying on or not working
door locks malfunctioning
and warning indicators on the instrument panel illuminating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the brake lights can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Brake lights staying on or not working
brake pedal feeling soft or spongy
and warning indicators on the instrument panel illuminating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the headlights can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Headlights burning out or melting
headlights not working
and warning indicators on the instrument panel illuminating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight connector can cause the headlights to malfunction or fail, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights intermittently fail or do not work at all
headlight bulbs burn out frequently
headlight connectors melt or corrode
headlight sockets overheat
and plastic components melt or break off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the brake lights can cause confusion for other drivers, leading to accidents or near-misses, as they may not be aware of the vehicle's intention to stop.
symptoms: Brake lights stay on continuously
brake lights turn off while driving
brake lights malfunction intermittently
and brake lights do not function at all.
